The paper deals with the formal verification of service-based applications, which is a topic that falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. The paper also introduces an extension of Linear Temporal Logic (LTL), which is a formal language used in programming languages (cs.PL) and logic (cs.LO). The paper also mentions the use of Bounded Model Checking (BMC), which is a technique used in hardware design (cs.DC) and software verification (cs.SE). Finally, the paper discusses the use of Satisfiability Modulo Theories (SMT), which is a technique used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and formal verification (cs.SE).
